  "text": "We found that networks composed of spiking neurons of this sort, when trained to respond to repeated sequences of sensory cues, generate temporally ordered patterns of neuronal activity consisting of brief steady states separated by sharp transitions that resemble those observed in functioning brains. We found that the present model could be used to control specific motor sequences in a brain-based device. The population activity pattern in this modeled neuronal system has similarities to those observed in primate pre-frontal cortex during multi-segmented limb movements [CITATION_1] .",
